                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Sanitize ticket body; flag instruction patterns"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Indirect prompt injection is structurally harder to defend than direct injection because the attack surface is the entire set of external content the system can read \u2014 not just the user's own input:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Attack vectors",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " span web pages, documents, emails, knowledge bases, code comments, and any other content an LLM agent or RAG system ingests."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Data exfiltration",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " via URL embedding turns the agent into an unwitting data leaker \u2014 without the user ever knowing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Defenses",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " require layered controls: content sanitization before ingestion, explicit role-labeling of untrusted content in prompts, URL allowlists on agent outbound calls, and output validation before any high-impact tool action executes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Because indirect injection exploits the agent's inherent trust in retrieved content, no single defense is sufficient. Assume that any content retrieved from the internet or user-submitted channels may be adversarially crafted \u2014 and design the system to limit the blast radius of a successful injection accordingly."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
